{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/b/getting-started-tdd-in-30-seconds-with-python","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Quick start to setup python script for Test Driven Development in 30 seconds</p>\n<p><strong>Time start!</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Install Python virtual environment for human ( yay! ) <a href=\"https://pipenv.readthedocs.io\"><code class=\"language-text\">pipenv</code></a></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">sudo pip install pipenv</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>create a directory and enter to it</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">mkdir my-tdd\ncd my-tdd</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Activate Python virtual environment, then the tool will automatically create it (if it‚Äôs not exist!)</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">pipenv shell</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Install <a href=\"https://docs.pytest.org/\">pytest</a> as a dev dependency</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">pipenv install pytest --dev</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>create file and test file in any place of the directory</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token comment\"># in lib.py</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">def</span> <span class=\"token function\">hello</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"hello\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># in lib_test.py or test_lib.py</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> lib\n<span class=\"token keyword\">def</span> <span class=\"token function\">test_hello</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">assert</span> lib<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>hello<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">==</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"hello\"</span></code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>let‚Äôs test</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">pytest</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Getting result!</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.dropbox.com/s/bgwfkw2d70jp4xk/Getting%20Started%20TDD%20in%2030%20Seconds%20with%20Python-02.png?raw=1\" alt=\"img\"></p>\n<p>The structure will be like this</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">lib.py\nlib_test.py\nPipfile\nPipfile.lock</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"extra\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#extra\" aria-label=\"extra permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><strong>Extra!</strong></h3>\n<p>You can use automatically test your code when the code's changed using <a href=\"https://github.com/joeyespo/pytest-watch\">pytest-watch</a></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">pipenv install pytest-watch</code></pre></div>\n<p>Let‚Äôs fun with TDD</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">ptw</code></pre></div>\n<p><strong>Time stoppppppppppp!</strong></p>\n<p>As I said before, this blog will end within 30 seconds</p>\n<p>Thanks guy, any question, pls comment</p>\n<p>Good bye, see you</p>\n<p>P.S. fastest blogging ever üôè</p>\n<hr>\n<p><em>Cross published at <a href=\"https://medium.com/@mildronize/getting-started-tdd-in-30-seconds-with-python-8113d6c94753\">Medium.com</a></em></p>","timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"Quick start to setup python script for Test Driven Development in 30 seconds Time start! Install Python virtual environment for human ( yay‚Ä¶","frontmatter":{"title":"Getting Started TDD in 30 Seconds with Python","date":null,"tags":["python","tdd","pipenv","pytest"]},"fields":{"slug":"/b/getting-started-tdd-in-30-seconds-with-python","date":"2018-09-08"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/b/getting-started-tdd-in-30-seconds-with-python","nexttitle":"‡πÑ‡∏î‡πâ 99 ‡∏Ñ‡∏∞‡πÅ‡∏ô‡∏ô‡∏à‡∏≤‡∏Å Google Insights & ‡πÄ‡∏£‡∏µ‡∏¢‡∏ô‡∏£‡∏π‡πâ‡∏Å‡∏≤‡∏£‡∏ó‡∏≥ web optimization","nextslug":"/b/99-score-google-insight-web-optimization","prevtitle":"Promise, Async, Await ‡∏Ç‡∏≠‡∏á JS ES6+ ‡∏â‡∏ö‡∏±‡∏ö‡∏™‡∏±‡πâ‡∏ô‡πÜ ‡πÑ‡∏°‡πà‡∏û‡∏π‡∏î‡πÄ‡∏¢‡∏≠‡∏∞ ‡πÄ‡∏à‡πá‡∏ö‡∏Ñ‡∏≠ ‡πÅ‡∏ñ‡∏° RxJS","prevslug":"/b/promise-async-await-rxjs-js-es-6"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}